$KLAC &quot;As of June 16, 2026, KLA Corporation (KLAC) is trading at $239.63, marking a sharp intraday drop of 6.55% (-$16.79). This pullback follows immense volatility tied to its fresh 10-for-1 forward stock split, which officially took effect on June 12, 2026. 
KLA holds a near-monopoly in semiconductor process control and metrology. The explosive growth of high-bandwidth memory (HBM) and complex AI chip designs requires absolute precision. Management projects its packaging-related process-control revenue will jump from ~$635 million in 2025 to $1 Billion by the end of 2026. 
During its latest Investor Day, KLA raised its long-term revenue CAGR targets to 13%–17% through 2030. Wall Street analysts are exceptionally optimistic about this long-term runway, with firms like JPMorgan forecasting a clear path toward significant earnings expansion by the end of the decade. Post-split targets average $194.67. Cantor Fitzgerald Maintained an Overweight rating, and a post-split target at $250.&quot;

$KLAC &quot;As of June 12, 2026, KLA Corporation (KLAC) has undergone a significant 10-for-1 stock split, resulting in a current trading price of approximately $248.31. Before the split, the stock reached all-time highs near $2,411. 
The long-term outlook remains positive, primarily driven by the company&#39;s dominance in the semiconductor process control market, where it holds a 56%+ market share. 
: Management recently raised its advanced packaging revenue guidance to $1 billion for 2026, fueled by surging demand for artificial intelligence hardware.&quot;

